   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="transcription">
            <p><milestone unit="passage" n="349.8-22"/>
<lb corresp="#b_y"/><w>kramtsa</w><w>santānäntse</w>
<lb corresp="#b_z"/><w>kos</w><w>yāmor<supplied>nta</supplied></w><gap reason="editorial"/><w>mokṣabhāgi</w><w>mäskeṃträ</w></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#b_y"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">through the krama ... of the santāna</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b_z"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">how many deeds? ... [these] are mokṣabhāgīyas</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note corresp="#b_y" type="lingcomment">The TB gloss with the two calques <hi>kram*</hi> and <hi>santāṃ*</hi> is remarkable: perhaps the glossator only wanted to indicate the case of the Sanskrit words.</note><note corresp="#b_y" type="philcomment">Glosses Skt. Abhidh-k-bh (<bibl><title corresp="ref:pradhan1975"/><citedRange>349</citedRange></bibl> l. 9 - for this section of the Abhidharmakośabhaṣya, cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:lavalleepoussin1980"/></bibl>: vol. IV, 178-9) <hi>krameṇa hi santān(a)sy(a)</hi> 'step by step ... of the series'.</note><note corresp="#b_z" type="philcomment"><hi>kos yāmor(nta)</hi> glosses Skt. Abhidh-k-bh (<bibl><title corresp="ref:pradhan1975"/><citedRange>349</citedRange></bibl> l. 13) <hi>kati karmaṇi</hi> (for <hi>karmāṇi</hi>) 'how many deeds?'. <hi>mokṣabhāgi mäskeṃträ</hi> glosses Skt. Abhidh-k-bh (<bibl><title corresp="ref:pradhan1975"/><citedRange>349</citedRange></bibl> l. 13-4) <hi>kati karmaṇi : triṇi karmā(ṇi)</hi> (for <hi>kati karmāṇi : triṇi karmā(ṇi)</hi> 'How many deeds? Three deeds.' This gloss clearly specifies which kinds of deed are discussed, namely <hi>mokṣabhāgīyas</hi> 'leading to final deliverance'.</note></p>
         </div>
